name: FFrameRate
doc:
A frame rate represented as a fraction comprising 2 integers: a numerator (number of frames), and a denominator (per second).
@note The full C++ class is located here: Engine\Source\Runtime\Core\Public\Misc\FrameRate.h

Numerator: The numerator of the framerate represented as a number of frames per second (e.g. 60 for 60 fps)
Denominator: The denominator of the framerate represented as a number of frames per second (e.g. 1 for 60 fps)
